Explanation:
The holes are marked as follows:

\begin{matrix}
(0,0) & (1,0) & (1,1) & (0,1)
\end{matrix}

We can cover these holes using two lines, as follows:

\begin{matrix}
(0,0) & (1,0) & (1,1) & (0,1) \\
(0,0) & (0.5,0.5) & (1,1) & (0.5,1)
\end{matrix}

Therefore, the smallest number of lines needed to cover the holes is two.

